The paper describes a deep learning approach for segmenting and counting cells in microscopy images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of a convolutional neural network and feature pyramid network also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of poor imaging quality, which could relate to information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
